  "texts": [
    "Otherwise, assume that p i is reachable from s through a sequence of operations each described by components in N.",
    "If p i+1 results from applying another valid operation (either from N 1, N 2, or N 3) to p i, then by the principle of induction, p i+1 is also reachable from s through a concatenated sequence of operations in N.",
    "By the established lemma, it is shown that every permutation p ∈ P can be reached from the correct sequence s through a series of allowable transformations represented by the components in N 1, N 2, and N 3.",
    "Therefore, we conclude that the set of deviated samples N defined is adequate to cover all samples in P.",
    "Theorem 2 (Necessity of N 1)."
